TATIONS (Patterns to Follow)\n\n#### Current Project Structure (RED Phase)\n\nThe backend is in the **RED phase** -- entities exist but no services, controllers, repositories, or feature modules have been implemented yet. The module structure:\n\n```\nbackend/src/modules/\n├── auth/entities/          (2 entity files only)\n│   ├── password-reset-token.entity.ts\n│   └── refresh-token.entity.ts\n├── favorites/entities/     (1 entity file only)\n│   └── favorite.entity.ts\n├── inquiries/entities/     (1 entity file only)\n│   └── inquiry.entity.ts\n├── properties/entities/    (4 entity files only)\n│   ├── amenity.entity.ts\n│   ├── property-amenity.entity.ts\n│   ├── property-photo.entity.ts\n│   └── property.entity.ts\n└── users/entities/         (1 entity file only)\n    └── user.entity.ts\n```\n\nThe `app.module.ts` is completely empty:\n```typescript\n@Module({\n  imports: [],\n  controllers: [],\n  providers: [],\n})\nexport class AppModule {}\n```\n\n#### The NestJS 4-Layer Architecture Pattern (from `.claude/nestjs/guides/architecture-overview.md`)\n\nEvery module should follow: **Controller -> Service -> Repository -> Entity**\n\nAll layers must extend the base classes in `backend/src/core/base/`:\n\n| Layer | Base Class | File | Key Features |\n|-------|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Entity | `BaseEntity` | `core/base/base.entity.ts` | UUID id, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt |\n| Repository | `BaseRepository` | `core/base/base.repository.ts` | findAll, findById, findOne, create, update, softDelete, delete, count |\n| Service | `BaseService` | `core/base/base.service.ts` | findByIdOrFail, findAll, create, update, remove, delete |\n| Controller | `BaseController` | `core/base/base.controller.ts` | POST, GET list, GET :id, PATCH :id, DELETE :id (all pre-wired) |\n\n#### Core Infrastructure Available\n\n| Feature | Files | Path |\n|---------|-------|------|\n| Guards | `JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`, `JwtStrategy` | `core/guards/` |\n| Decorators | `@Public()`, `@Roles()`, `@CurrentUser()` | `core/decorators/` |\n| Filters | `HttpExceptionFilter`, `AllExceptionsFilter` | `core/filters/` |\n| Interceptors | `TransformInterceptor`, `LoggingInterceptor`, etc. | `core/interceptors/` |\n| Response DTO | `ResponsePayloadDto`, `SuccessResponseDto`, `ErrorResponseDto` | `shared/dtos/` |\n| Pagination | `PaginationDto`, `PaginatedResponseDto` | `shared/dtos/` |\n| Enums | `RoleEnum` (renter/admin) | `common/enums/role.enum.ts` |\n\n**Auth pattern**: JWT via httpOnly cookies, `@Public()` marks unauthenticated routes, `@Roles('admin')` restricts to admins.\n\n#### Folder Structure Pattern for a New Module\n\nBased on the architecture guide, a complete amenities module would need:\n\n```\nbackend/src/modules/amenities/\n├── dto/\n│   ├── create-amenity.dto.ts\n│   └── update-amenity.dto.ts\n├── amenities.controller.ts\n├── amenities.service.ts\n├── amenities.repository.ts\n└── amenities.module.ts\n```\n\n(And the `amenity.entity.ts` should be moved from `properties/entities/` to `amenities/entities/`.)\n\n---\n\n### 7. SUMMARY OF FINDINGS\n\n| What | Status | Key File(s) |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| Dedicated amenities module | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n| Amenity entity | **Exists** in `properties/entities/` | `backend/src/modules/properties/entities/amenity.entity.ts` |\n| PropertyAmenity junction entity | **Exists** | `backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property-amenity.entity.ts` |\n| Amenities e2e tests | **Written (RED phase)** | `backend/test/e2e/amenities.e2e-spec.ts` (4 endpoints, 24 test cases) |\n| Test fixtures (seed + helpers) | **Exists** | `backend/test/fixtures/property.fixture.ts` |\n| Test app factory (entity reg) | **Exists** | `backend/test/setup/test-app.factory.ts` |\n| API spec (complete) | **Exists** | `.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_API.md` (lines 1188-1336) |\n| API spec (simplified, incomplete) | **Exists** | `.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API.md` (lines 1083-1138) |\n| Database schema doc | **Exists** (2 copies) | `.claude-project/{,nestfind/}docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md` |\n| Knowledge doc | **Exists** (2 copies) | `.claude-project/{,nestfind/}docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md` |\n| DTOs | **Do not exist** | N/A |\n| Service | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n| Controller | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n| Repository | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n| Module | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n| MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml | **Does not exist** | N/A |\n\n**Bottom line**: The Amenity entity, junction table, e2e tests, test fixtures, and full API spec are all defined. What is **missing** is the 4-layer NestJS implementation: DTOs, Repository, Service, Controller, and Module. The patterns to follow are clearly defined in the core base classes and architecture guide.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1c02c81caffetwDDNHy3gYKYJB","sessionId":"ses_1c02c44bcffe5ctLW4BLkA59bj","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore amenities requirements","time":{"start":1779187301191,"end":1779187622913}},"id":"prt_e3fd3a32b001IBPBE3TItL5592","sessionID":"ses_1c02c81caffetwDDNHy3gYKYJB","messageID":"msg_e3fd382b1001459Yy4XCqSR5wo"}}
